// FIXTURE (not compiled): a traceability catalog mapping in-scope AC ids to the
// test that covers them, plus the test bodies. The traceability gate must fail
// for BOTH classes of defect present here:
//   - FIXTURE-AC-MISSING: an in-scope AC with NO mapped test at all.
//   - FIXTURE-AC-VACUOUS: an AC mapped to a test whose body is a placeholder
//     (assertion-free / #expect(true)) — "named but vacuous".
// FIXTURE-AC-GOOD is the only one that should pass.

@Test  // covers: FIXTURE-AC-GOOD
func goodHasRealAssertion() {
    let produced = computeUnderTest()
    #expect(produced == "expected-value")
}

@Test  // covers: FIXTURE-AC-VACUOUS
func vacuousPlaceholder() {
    // Placeholder body — no behavior is asserted. The gate must reject this.
    #expect(Bool(true))
}

// NOTE: FIXTURE-AC-MISSING is intentionally listed as in-scope below but has NO
// @Test mapped to it, so the gate must flag the absent mapping.
//
// in-scope-acs: FIXTURE-AC-GOOD, FIXTURE-AC-VACUOUS, FIXTURE-AC-MISSING
